      </div>
      
      
      
      
      
      <div class='message assistant d-4 d-11' data-message-id='d-14' id='msg-d-14'>
          <div class='header'>
              <span>🤖 Assistant</span>
              <div class='header-info'>
                  <div class='timestamp-row'>
                      <span class='timestamp' data-timestamp='2025-07-03T16:08:07.874907Z'>2025-07-03 16:08:07</span>
                  </div>
                  
                  <span class='token-usage'>Input: 45 | Output: 110</span>
                  
              </div>
          </div>
          <div class='debug-info'>msg_010</div>
          <div class='content markdown'><div class="assistant-text markdown"><p>Perfect! As you can see, the <code>@repeat(3)</code> decorator successfully made the <code>greet</code> function execute three times, printing &quot;Hello, Alice!&quot; three times.</p>
  <p>This demonstrates the power of parameterized decorators - you can customize their behavior by passing arguments to the decorator factory. Some common use cases include:</p>
  <ul>
  <li><strong>Timing decorators</strong>: <code>@time_it(units='ms')</code></li>
  <li><strong>Retry decorators</strong>: <code>@retry(max_attempts=3, delay=1)</code></li>
  <li><strong>Authentication decorators</strong>: <code>@require_role('admin')</code></li>
  <li><strong>Caching decorators</strong>: <code>@cache(ttl=300)</code></li>
  </ul>
  <p>The pattern is always the same: decorator factory → decorator → wrapper function.</p>
  </div></div>
          
      </div>
      
      
      
      
      
